text:
i ordered roti prata… and keep insisting i want fish curry only, in the end they give me 2 different color curry…

When i asked, you sure you give me fish curry for both? He said yes.

I go home and tried, one fish and one chicken curry.. Wa lau.. i believe this lie again and again…

It’s not the first time like that already
now i have settle myself with the chicken curry because my family members only love fish curry

my entire day is ruined……………. or just less perfect?
fish curry come and save me!!!!!!!

Grab ordered plain prata, cheese prata and egg prata. Only the plain prata is edible. Cheese is using cheddar, not nice. Egg was not tasty. Gravy doesn’t have much spicy notes. Not satisfying. Not many good prata places in Punggol.

This is a spot for prata in Punggol. It's served crispy and hot with either fish or chicken curry, which is a nice change from the usual dal curry. The service is decent and can be friendly at times. Just keep in mind that the stall only accepts cash.

Never order from them if you’re vegetarian. I had the worst experience of my life. I received seafood fried rice when I ordered “no meat, vegetarian” and each time I indicate give dal (vegetarian gravy), I get fish curry. I am very unhappy. All other Srisun seem fine, it’s just this Punggol.
The service is ok but the food is horrid! We ordered food worth $50 but ended up wasting most of it. Such a disappointment. Please do not waste your money here. Only Prata was ok.
